Only seven survivors made it back to shore in "extremely dire conditions" and have been admitted to hospital, it added.
So far, 11 bodies have been retrieved by the Libyan red Crescent and the local police, while the seven survivors are in hospital, the IOM said. The vessel was reportedly heading to Europe, the IOM said. Libya has become a major launching point for migrants seeking to reach Europe via a dangerous route across the desert and over the Mediterranean. --BBC\Reuters--